implementation:
  usage:
    description: Takes a high-level goal and breaks it into a structured plan of subgoals and specific actions. Can be iterative,
      refining the plan as new information becomes available.
    example: &id001
      high_level_goal: Write a research paper on climate change impact on agriculture.
      GoalDecompositionPlanner_output: "<GoalDecompositionPlanner goal='Write research paper...'>\n  Plan:\n  1. Subgoal:\
        \ Conduct Literature Review\n     - Action: Search academic databases (keywords: climate change, agriculture, impact)\n\
        \     - Action: Read and synthesize 20 relevant papers\n     - Action: Identify key themes and gaps\n  2. Subgoal:\
        \ Formulate Research Question & Hypothesis\n     - Action: Refine scope based on literature review\n     - Action:\
        \ Draft specific research question\n  3. Subgoal: Outline Paper Structure\n     - Action: Create section headings\
        \ (Intro, Methods, Results, Discussion, Conclusion)\n  4. Subgoal: Draft Paper Sections\n     - ... (further decomposition)\n\
        \  5. Subgoal: Revise and Edit\n     - ...\n</GoalDecompositionPlanner>"
    explanation: This sigil enables systematic problem-solving. Instead of attempting a complex goal monolithically, it breaks
      it into smaller, more achievable parts. This is fundamental for any sophisticated task execution, from writing code
      to planning a project.
